# .dockerignore — allowlist build context for a minimal, reproducible image.
#
# This file is an ALLOWLIST, not a denylist: it starts by excluding the
# ENTIRE build context with `*`, then re-includes ONLY the files the image
# build actually needs:
#
#   Cargo.toml   (manifest; also declares `readme = "README.md"`)
#   Cargo.lock   (required for `cargo build --release --locked`)
#   src/         (the Rust sources)
#   README.md    (referenced by Cargo.toml `readme`, so the build needs it)
#
# Leading-`*` allowlisting is deliberate defense-in-depth: any unanticipated
# credential-bearing file (credentials.yaml, secrets.toml, id_rsa, *.pem,
# *.key, a local .env, a Matrix session store, the .git history, etc.) is
# excluded by default and can never leak into a build layer / `docker history`
# unless it is explicitly re-included below.
#
# Order matters: in classic-builder dockerignore semantics a later rule wins,
# so all `!`-negations MUST come after the `*` catch-all, and a directory must
# be re-included before its contents (`!src/` then `!src/**`).

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. Exclude everything.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
*

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2. Belt-and-suspenders: explicitly deny secret/credential patterns.
#    Already covered by the `*` above, but listed so the intent is documented
#    and so the denylist survives if the `*` is ever removed.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
**/.env
**/.env.*
**/*.pem
**/*.key
**/*.crt
**/*.p12
**/*.pfx
**/id_rsa*
**/.netrc
**/*.session.json
matrix-mcp-session.json
**/*.sqlite
**/*.sqlite-shm
**/*.sqlite-wal
**/*.db
matrix-store/
store/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 3. Re-include ONLY what the build needs.
#    `!src/` re-includes the directory entry; `!src/**` re-includes its
#    contents (required under classic-builder semantics — `!src/` alone would
#    not resurrect the files inside it).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
!Cargo.toml
!Cargo.lock
!src/
!src/**
!README.md
